 senator thrown in jail. They stole valuable tech prototypes. They swung an election, for Christ's sake.$NL;WEST: What's your point?$NL;KENT: My point is: when they worked with The Elephant, people got screwed. Powerful people. Washington people.$NL;WEST: And now there's a secret Anti-Payday Committee? Come on.$NL;KENT: No. But there are a whole bunch of politicians and lawmakers who want to see the Gang get theirs. Somebody's going to figure that out. They're gonna connect the dots, and when they do, they'll have an entire shadow network of power at their disposal with one purpose. One goal.$NL;WEST: ...Take down the Payday Gang?$NL;KENT: Take down the Payday Gang.$NL;WEST: I guess there are worse conspiracies.$NL;KENT: My thoughts exactly.$NL;WEST: Oh, by the way, I got an email from some agent named ''Stone-''$NL;KENT: She's some newbie fresh out of Quantico. Wants access to the Clown Files. She's obsessed, you'll get about a hundred emails from her a week. Just ignore them.$NL;WEST: She'll probably have my old job soon.$NL;KENT: Fine. Let her get shot at if she wants to.$NL;WEST: Haha! That I won't miss.",
